tia}} [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]]\n| bgcolor=\"#ddffdd\"|3\u20130 ([[Overtime (sports)#Association football|a.e.t.]])\n| bgcolor=\"#ffdddd\"|0\u20131\n| 3\u20131\n|-\n| {{Tooltip|QF|Quarter-finals}}\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Germany}} [[Eintracht Frankfurt]]\n| bgcolor=\"#ddffdd\"|4\u20132\n| bgcolor=\"#ffdddd\"|0\u20132\n| 4\u20134 ([[Away goals rule|a]])\n|-\n| rowspan=3|[[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League|2019\u201320]]\n| rowspan=3 align=\"left\"|UEFA Champions League\n| rowspan=3|{{Tooltip|GS|Group stage}}\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Germany}} [[RB Leipzig]]\n| bgcolor=\"#ffdddd\"|1\u20132\n| bgcolor=\"#ffffdd\"|2\u20132\n| rowspan=3|\n|-\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Russia}} [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]]\n| bgcolor=\"#ddffdd\"|3\u20130\n| bgcolor=\"#ffdddd\"|1\u20133\n|-\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|France}} [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]]\n| bgcolor=\"#ddffdd\"|2\u20131\n| bgcolor=\"#ffdddd\"|1\u20133\n|-\n| [[2019\u201320 UEFA Europa League|2019\u201320]]\n| align=\"left\"|UEFA Europa League\n| {{Tooltip|R32|Round of 32}}\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Ukraine}} [[FC Shakhtar Donetsk|Shakhtar Donetsk]]\n| bgcolor=\"#ffffdd\"|3\u20133\n| bgcolor=\"#ffdddd\"|1\u20132\n| 4\u20135\n|}\n<small>Last updated: 27 February 2020<br />Note: Benfica score is always listed first.</small>\n\n==Records==\n[[File:Eusebio (1963).jpg|200px|right|thumb|[[Eus\u00e9bio]] is the Benfica player with the [[List of S.L. Benfica records and statistics#Topscorers in Europe|highest goal tally]] in international competitions, with 56 scored.]]\n{{updated|27 February 2020}}\n{{Main|List of S.L. Benfica records and statistics}}\nBenfica was the first Portuguese side to reach the final of the European Cup, the first to win it and the only one to this day to win the trophy in consecutive years.{{sfn|Pereira|2011|p=68}} In the 1960s, they reached the final five times, more than any other team, surpassing Real Madrid and Milan, who only reached three each.<ref>{{cite web|author=Jamie Rainbow|title=A potted history of Benfica|url=https://www.worldsoccer.com/blogs/a-potted-history-of-benfica-part-one-341908|website=World Soccer|access-date=19 September 2015|date=3 August 2013}}</ref> Their ten European finals are also a domestic record,<ref>{{cite news|title=\u00c1guias refor\u00e7am s\u00e9timo lugar do \"ranking\" de finais europeias|trans-title=Eagles strengthen seventh place in European finals \"ranking\"|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/aguias-reforcam-setimo-lugar-do-ranking-de-finais-europeias-880804|access-date=19 September 2015|work=Record|date=1 May 2014|language=pt}}</ref> and with 39 participations in the Champions League (formerly the European Cup), only Real Madrid has played more seasons in the competition.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/MultimediaFiles/Download/EuroExperience/competitions/Publications/02/28/56/90/2285690_DOWNLOAD.pdf#page=2|title=2015/16 UEFA Champions League statistics handbook - All-Time records \u2013 All-time records 1955\u20132015|website=[[UEFA]]|pages=2\u20133|format=PDF|access-date=27 January 2016}}</ref>\n\n*Most appearances in European competition: [[Luis\u00e3o]], 127<ref name=\"UEFA profile\"/>\n*Most goals in European competition: [[Eus\u00e9bio]], 56<ref name=\"UEFA profile\"/>\n*First European match: [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] 3\u20131 Benfica in the European Cup, on 19 September 1957<ref>{{cite news|title=History at UEFA.com|url=https://www.uefa.com/teamsandplayers/teams/club=50147/profile/index.html|access-date=19 May 2018|work=[[UEFA]]}}</ref>\n*Biggest win: Benfica 10\u20130 [[Stade Dudelange]] in the European Cup, on 5 October 1965<ref name=\"UEFA profile\"/>\n*First goal in European competition: [[Francisco Palmeiro]], in the 40th minute against Sevilla, on 19 September 1957<ref>{{cite book|last=Pereira|first=Lu\u00eds Miguel|date=May 2014|title=B\u00edblia do Benfica|trans-title=Benfica bible|language=pt|edition=1st|location=Portugal|publisher=Prime Books|page=1381|isbn=978-989-655-215-2}}</ref>\n*Biggest defeat: [[Celta de Vigo|Celta Vigo]] 7\u20130 Benfica in the UEFA Cup, on 25 November 1999<ref name=\"UEFA profile\"/>\n*Highest European home attendance: 110,000, against [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] in the European Cup, on 18 April 1990{{sfn|Pereira|2011|p=63}}\n\n===By competition===\n{| class=\"wikitable unsortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ S.L. Benfica record in European football by competition<ref name=\"Stats by competition\">{{cite web|title=Benfica Competitions History|url=https://www.playmakerstats.com/team_compets.php?id=4|website=playmakerstats.com|publisher=Playmaker Stats|access-date=21 February 2020}}</ref>\n!scope=\"col\"|Competition\n!scope=\"col\"|{{Tooltip|Pld|Games Played}}\n!scope=\"col\"|{{Tooltip|W|Won}}\n!scope=\"col\"|{{Tooltip|D|Drawn}}\n!scope=\"col\"|{{Tooltip|L|Lost}}\n!scope=\"col\"|{{Tooltip|GF|Goals For}}\n!scope=\"col\"|{{Tooltip|GA|Goals Against}}\n!scope=\"col\"|{{Tooltip|GD|Goals Difference}}\n!scope=\"col\"|Win%{{efn|Win% is [[Rounding|rounded]] to [[Decimal|two decimal places]].}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|[[UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League / European Cup]]\n{{WDL|258|114|59|85|for=416|against=299|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|[[UEFA Cup Winners' Cup]]\n{{WDL|42|21|12|9|for=67|against=34|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|[[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League / UEFA Cup]]\n{{WDL|127|64|28|35|for=202|against=141|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|[[Inter-Cities Fairs Cup]]\n{{WDL|4|2|1|1|for=7|against=5|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|[[Intercontinental Cup (football)|Intercontinental Cup]]\n{{WDL|5|1|0|4|for=6|against=15|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!Total\n{{WDLtot|436|202|100|134|for=698|against=494|diff=yes}}\n|}\n\n===By country===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable collapsible collapsed plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ S.L. Benfica record in continental football by country<ref name=\"Stats international hist\">{{cite web|title=Sport Lisboa e Benfica International history|url=https://www.thefinalball.com/team_international.php?ond=&grp=2&pais_adv=0&id=4|website=Thefinalball.com|access-date=4 August 2016}}</ref>\n!scope=\"col\"|Country\n!scope=\"col\"|{{Tooltip|Pld|Games Played}}\n!scope=\"col\"|{{Tooltip|W|Won}}\n!scope=\"col\"|{{Tooltip|D|Drawn}}\n!scope=\"col\"|{{Tooltip|L|Lost}}\n!scope=\"col\"|{{Tooltip|GF|Goals For}}\n!scope=\"col\"|{{Tooltip|GA|Goals Against}}\n!scope=\"col\"|{{Tooltip|GD|Goals Difference}}\n!scope=\"col\"|Win%{{efn|Win% is [[Rounding|rounded]] to [[Decimal|two decimal places]].}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Albania}}\n{{WDL|2|2|0|0|for=7|against=0|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Austria}}\n{{WDL|8|5|3|0|for=21|against=5|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Belarus}}\n{{WDL|2|2|0|0|for=4|against=1|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Belgium}}\n{{WDL|19|11|4|4|for=29|against=17|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Brazil}}\n{{WDL|2|0|0|2|for=4|against=8|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Bulgaria}}\n{{WDL|6|4|2|0|for=13|against=7|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Croatia}}\n{{WDL|7|4|2|1|for=9|against=2|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Cyprus}}\n{{WDL|2|2|0|0|for=4|against=0|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Czech Republic}}\n{{WDL|6|2|3|1|for=6|against=5|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Denmark}}\n{{WDL|14|12|2|0|for=29|against=7|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|England}}\n{{WDL|36|11|6|19|for=48|against=62|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Finland}}\n{{WDL|2|0|1|1|for=2|against=4|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|France}}\n{{WDL|30|15|7|8|for=38|against=29|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Germany}}\n{{WDL|49|14|14|21|for=54|against=79|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Greece}}\n{{WDL|19|11|2|6|for=28|against=21|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Hungary}}\n{{WDL|14|9|2|3|for=37|against=13|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Iceland}}\n{{WDL|2|1|1|0|for=8|against=1|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Israel}}\n{{WDL|4|2|0|2|for=10|against=7|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Italy}}\n{{WDL|31|9|5|17|for=29|against=40|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Kazakhstan}}\n{{WDL|2|1|1|0|for=4|against=2|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Luxembourg}}\n{{WDL|4|4|0|0|for=28|against=2|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Malta}}\n{{WDL|2|2|0|0|for=10|against=0|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Netherlands}}\n{{WDL|25|10|9|6|for=39|against=28|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Northern Ireland}}\n{{WDL|8|5|3|0|for=21|against=7|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Norway}}\n{{WDL|6|5|0|1|for=11|against=4|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Poland}}\n{{WDL|4|2|2|0|for=7|against=2|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Portugal}}\n{{WDL|2|1|0|1|for=2|against=2|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Republic of Ireland}}\n{{WDL|2|2|0|0|for=6|against=1|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Romania}}\n{{WDL|12|7|4|1|for=13|against=5|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Russia}}\n{{WDL|19|7|4|8|for=21|against=23|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Scotland}}\n{{WDL|10|6|1|3|for=14|against=9|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Serbia}}\n{{WDL|2|1|0|1|for=4|against=3|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Slovakia}}\n{{WDL|2|2|0|0|for=5|against=0|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Slovenia}}\n{{WDL|4|3|1|0|for=17|against=2|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Spain}}\n{{WDL|25|6|8|11|for=28|against=38|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Sweden}}\n{{WDL|8|3|2|3|for=15|against=9|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Switzerland}}\n{{WDL|7|3|3|1|for=14|against=8|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Turkey}}\n{{WDL|17|7|6|4|for=28|against=15|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Ukraine}}\n{{WDL|12|7|1|4|for=22|against=9|diff=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Uruguay}}\n{{WDL|3|1|0|2|for=2|against=7|diff=yes}}\n|}\n\n===Finals===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Competition\n! Opposing team\n! Score\n! Venue\n|-\n| bgcolor=Gold|[[1961 European Cup Final|1961]]\n| [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup]]\n| {{flagicon|Spain|1945}} [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]]\n| 3\u20132\n| {{flagicon|Switzerland}} [[Wankdorf Stadium]], [[Bern]]\n|-\n| bgcolor=Gold|[[1962 European Cup Final|1962]]\n| [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup]]\n| {{flagicon|Spain|1945}} [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]]\n| 5\u20133<ref name=\"Real Madrid v Benfica\"/>\n| {{flagicon|Netherlands}} [[Olympic Stadium (Amsterdam)|Olympic Stadium]], [[Amsterdam]]\n|-\n| bgcolor=Silver|[[1963 European Cup Final|1963]]\n| [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup]]\n| {{flagicon|Italy}} [[A.C. Milan|Milan]]\n| 1\u20132<ref name=\"Milan v Benfica\"/>\n| {{flagicon|England}} [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], [[London]]\n|-\n| bgcolor=Silver|[[1965 European Cup Final|1965]]\n| [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup]]\n| {{flagicon|Italy}} [[Inter Milan]]\n| 0\u20131\n| {{flagicon|Italy}} [[San Siro]], [[Milan]]\n|-\n| bgcolor=Silver|[[1968 European Cup Final|1968]]\n| [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup]]\n| {{flagicon|England}} [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]]\n| 1\u20134 ([[Overtime (sports)#Association football|aet]])\n| {{flagicon|England}} [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], [[London]]\n|-\n| bgcolor=Silver|[[1983 UEFA Cup Final|1983]]\n| [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]]\n| {{flagicon|Belgium}} [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]]\n| 1\u20132\n| Two-legged\n|-\n| bgcolor=Silver|[[1988 European Cup Final|1988]]\n| [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup]]\n