{"title_page": "Results of the 1964 Swedish general election", "text_new": "'''[[Sweden]]''' held a [[1964 Swedish general election|general election]] on 20 September 1964.<ref name=SCB>{{cite web|url=http://share.scb.se/ov9993/data/historisk%20statistik/SOS%201911-%2FValstatistiken%2FRiksdagsmannavalen%20(SOS)%201909-1968%2FValstatistik-Riksdagsmannavalen-1961-1964-I.pdf|title=Riksdagsmannavalen \u00e5ren 1961-1964. I = The election to the Riksdag during the years 1961-1964. I - Valstatistik-Riksdagsmannavalen- 1961-1964-I.pdf|publisher=[[Statistiska Centralbyr\u00e5n]]|language=sv|accessdate=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Results==\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:right\n!Party\n!Votes\n!%\n!Seats\n!+/\u2013\n|-\n|align=left|[[Swedish Social Democratic Party]]||2,006,923||47.3||113||\u20131\n|-\n|align=left|[[Liberal People's Party (Sweden)|People's Party]]||720,733||17.0||43||+3\n|-\n|align=left|[[Moderate Party|Rightist Party]]||582,609||13.7||33||\u20136\n|-\n|align=left|[[Centre Party (Sweden)|Centre Party]]||559,632||13.2||35||+1\n|-\n|align=left|[[Left Party (Sweden)|Communist Party of Sweden]]||221,746||5.2||8||+3\n|-\n|align=left|[[Christian Democrats (Sweden)|Christian Democratic Unity]]||75,389||1.8||0||New\n|-\n|align=left|Civic Unity{{ref label|reference_name_A|a|a}}||64,807||1.5||1||New\n|-\n|align=left|Middle Parties{{ref label|reference_name_B|b|b}}||13,557||0.3||0||New\n|-\n|align=left|Other parties||384||0.0||0||0\n|-\n|align=left|Valid votes||4,245,780||-||-||-\n|-\n|align=left|Invalid/blank votes||27,815||\u2013||\u2013||\u2013\n|-\n|align=left|'''Total'''||'''4,273,595'''||'''100'''||'''233'''||'''+1'''\n|-\n|align=left|Registered voters/turnout||5,095,850||83.9||\u2013||\u2013\n|-\n|align=left colspan=5|Source: Nohlen & St\u00f6ver\n|}\n\n{{note label|reference_name_A|a|a}} Civic Unity was a joint list of the three right-wing parties in [[Malm\u00f6]]. One of its elected candidates was a member of the Centre Party, but sat as an independent.<ref>Nohlen & St\u00f6ver, p1872</ref>\n\n{{note label|reference_name_B|b|b}} The Middle Parties was a joint list of the [[Centre Party (Sweden)|Centre Party]] and [[Liberal People's Party (Sweden)|People's Party]] that contested some constituencies.<ref>Nohlen & St\u00f6ver, p1861</ref>\n{{Bar box\n|title=Popular vote\n|titlebar=#ddd\n|width=600px\n|barwidth=350px\n|bars=\n{{Bar percent|S|{{Swedish Social Democratic Party/meta/color}}|47.27}}\n{{Bar percent|FP|{{Liberals (Sweden)/meta/color}}|16.98}}\n{{Bar percent|H|{{Moderate Party/meta/color}}|13.72}}\n{{Bar percent|C|{{Centre Party (Sweden)/meta/color}}|13.18}}\n{{Bar percent|SKP|{{Left Party (Sweden)/meta/color}}|5.22}}\n{{Bar percent|KD|{{Christian Democrats (Sweden)/meta/color}}|1.78}}\n{{Bar percent|Med-Sam|#6E6E6E|1.52}}\n{{Bar percent|Others|{{Other/meta/color}}|0.33}}\n}}\n{{Bar box\n|title=Parliament seats\n|titlebar=#ddd\n|width=600px\n|barwidth=350px\n|bars=\n{{Bar percent|S|{{Swedish Social Democratic Party/meta/color}}|48.50}}\n{{Bar percent|FP|{{Liberals (Sweden)/meta/color}}|18.45}}\n{{Bar percent|C|{{Centre Party (Sweden)/meta/color}}|15.02}}\n{{Bar percent|H|{{Moderate Party/meta/color}}|14.16}}\n{{Bar percent|SKP|{{Left Party (Sweden)/meta/color}}|3.43}}\n{{Bar percent|Med-Sam|#6E6E6E|0.43}}\n}}\n\n==Constituency results==\nThe results of the various constituency coalitions between the centre-right parties have all been listed under \"C/F/H\".\n\n===Percentage share===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=text-align:right\n!Location\n!Land\n!Turnout\n!Share\n!Votes\n![[Social Democrats (Sweden)|S]]\n![[Liberals (Sweden)|FP]]\n![[Moderate Party (Sweden)|H]]\n![[Centre Party (Sweden)|C]]\n![[Left Party (Sweden)|K]]\n!C/F/H\n![[Christian Democrats (Sweden)|KDS]]\n!Other\n!Left\n!Right\n|-\n|align=left|[[Blekinge County|Blekinge]]\n| [[G\u00f6taland|G]]\n| 81.9\n| 1.9\n| 81,038\n| 50.6\n| 18.5\n| 13.1\n| 13.2\n| 4.6\n| 0.0\n| 0.1\n| 0.0\n| 55.2\n| 44.8\n|-\n|align=left|[[Gothenburg and Bohus Count